<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1084" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1084">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6463/5–545: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">San Francisco</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-05">May 5,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received May 5—10:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>13. For Clayton. Soong has not raised with me the question of assistance in
                        connection with the Yangtze Power Project referred to in your No. 31, May 4.
                        He has said, however, that he will raise all the economic matters in which
                        he is interested when he is in Washington next week.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>